editorialSummary.text: Laid-back restaurant & bar with a terrace offering traditional Mexican cuisine & cocktails.

originalText.text: Ok this place is dope dope!! We happened to go when it was brunch and everything was delicious! The dj was on point, our waitress was on point and the food from beginning to end was on point! My only complaints were how hot it got. They had fans everywhere in the ceiling but didn't turn them on. My other one was while the food was delicious it wasn't much of a selection. Aside from that I will def be back but most likely after brunch hours.

originalText.text:
I was so happy to be invited to this restaurant. When my friend and I arrived, we parked on the street nearby. We walked up and saw there was indoor and outdoor seating. It was raining so no one was outside. We walked in and were greeted by the female manager. I totally forgot her name, but she was nice and accommodating. She sat us, and Erica was our server. While new, she was on point! I loved her energy, and she was super attentive.

We started with the sangria pitcher, and the awesome female bartender hooked us up with some specialty cocktails. The frozen margarita I had was so great! My friend enjoyed her coconut cocktail! For our appetizers, we both got wings, and the sweet chili wings were ok.

Now it was time for entrées and I got the fajitas which were tasty and plenty to eat. My friend got the steak and eggs and she enjoyed them! The vibe was great, the DJ was off the chain, and the service was good as well! I really enjoyed my time!

originalText.text: Had the pleasure of being apart of a tasting of the whole brunch menu so we had a little bit of everything. What I throughly enjoyed the most out of the whole menu were The Chicken Wings, Queso Fundido, Ceasar Salad, Steak & Eggs, The Churro French Toast and The Chicken Fajita. They also offered pitchers of Sangria and/or Mimosa which I would recommend the Sangria. The waitress which is also a bartender made her specialty drink for us as well which was very delicious as well as a Passion Fruit Margarita that I tried. All and all I would come here again and also try the other restaurants which are under the same ownership as this one.

originalText.text: I really like this place not gna lie, it’s always a good vibe. The food is usually good and the DJs are usually good as well. Tonight we had an issue where my sister forgot her ID but she had a pic of it on her phone and they would not let her in‼️ PEOPLE OUT THERE IF YOU DON’T HAVE YOUR PHYSICAL ID THEY WON’T LET YOU IN‼️ they gave us a warm time but after bout 30 mins they finally did. That was a bummer but we still made the best of the night.

originalText.text: I'm  not sure if we came too early, but my daughter and I were the only ones in the place. Another couple came around 6ish, but that was about it til we left and headed over to Cantina's. I wasn't a fan of the chrizo nachos, and I love nachos... Did I mention love nachos. It wasn't making it that day.   My daughter enjoyed her quesadillas, tho. Happy Hour drinks could have been better, the flavor in the frozen margarita's started to clump up. I will not give it a bad review, I guess we came on the wrong that that's all.
